# Composable by default

**Canonical:** `docs/ecosystem/composable-by-default.md`

## Required

- **`src/lib.li`** exports composable **`def`** APIs: start / stop / ready (or domain-equivalent verbs).
- Every exported **`def`** (and each **`extern proc`**) has `requires`, `ensures`, `decreases` (strict-by-default).
- **`src/main.li`** is a thin demo that imports the library — not the only entry point.
- Package tests **import** `lib.li` (see `li-tests/composable/` and skill `composable-li-library`).

## Forbidden

- Substantial feature logic only in `main.li` with no importable API.
- Hidden global server/runner state instead of explicit handles.
- C-only or script-only entry with no Li `lib.li` surface.
- Claiming a service package is “done” when only a CLI binary exists.

## httpd

`packages/li-httpd` targets `httpd_serve` / `httpd_stop` / `httpd_ready` on `HttpdHandle`. **Do not claim M1 complete** until [httpd-prerequisites.md](../../docs/ecosystem/httpd-prerequisites.md) P0 rows are green and routing tests exist.
